{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2018}} {{Infobox football biography |name = Idrissa Gueye |image = Idrissa Gueye (cropped).jpg |image_size = 150 |caption = Gueye warming up for [[Senegal national football team|Senegal]] at the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]] |fullname = Idrissa Gana Gueye<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/612828 |title=Updated squads for 2017/18 Premier League confirmed |publisher=Premier League |date=2 February 2018 |accessdate=11 February 2018}}</ref> |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1989|9|26|df=y}}<ref name=NFT/> |birth_place = [[Dakar]], Senegal<ref name=NFT/> |height = 1.74 m<ref name=NFT/> |position = [[Midfielder#Defensive midfielder|Defensive midfielder]]<ref name=NFT/> |currentclub = [[Everton F.C.|Everton]] |clubnumber = 17 |youthyears1 = |youthclubs1 = |years1 = 2007–2008 |clubs1 = [[Diambars FC|Diambars]] |caps1 = |goals1 = |years2 = 2008–2010 |clubs2 = [[Lille OSC|Lille B]] |caps2 = 55 |goals2 = 2 |years3 = 2010–2015 |clubs3 = [[Lille OSC|Lille]] |caps3 = 134 |goals3 = 5 |years4 = 2015–2016 |clubs4 = [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] |caps4 = 35 |goals4 = 0 |years5 = 2016– |clubs5 = [[Everton F.C.|Everton]] |caps5 = 89 |goals5 = 3 |nationalyears1 = 2012 |nationalteam1 = [[Senegal national under-23 football team|Senegal Olympic]] |nationalcaps1 = 1 |nationalgoals1 = 0 |nationalyears2 = 2011– |nationalteam2 = [[Senegal national football team|Senegal]] |nationalcaps2 = 56 |nationalgoals2 = 2 |club-update = 13:48, 27 February 2019 (UTC) |nationalteam-update = 22:18, 17 November 2018 (UTC) }} '''Idrissa Gana Gueye''' (born 26 September 1989) is a Senegalese professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Midfielder#Defensive midfielder|defensive midfielder]] for {{English football updater|Everton}} club [[Everton F.C.|Everton]] and the [[Senegal national football team|Senegal national team]].
==Club career== ===Early career=== [[File:Corchia, Eto'o, Gueye.JPG|thumb|right|Gueye, then playing for Lille, and [[Samuel Eto'o]]]] Born in [[Dakar]], Gueye spent his early career in Senegal for [[Diambars FC|Diambars]] before joining French club [[Lille OSC|Lille]] in 2008.<ref name = NFT>{{NFT player|pid=45752|accessdate=2 July 2015}}</ref> He broke through into the first team in the 2010–11 season, in which Lille won [[Ligue 1]], and became a regular starter in the league and the [[UEFA Champions League]] over the following four seasons.<ref name = "EFC">{{cite web|url=http://www.evertonfc.com/players/i/ig/idrissa-gana-gueye|title=Profile|accessdate=22 September 2016|publisher=Everton F.C.}}</ref>
===Aston Villa=== On 10 July 2015, Gueye joined English [[Premier League]] club [[Aston Villa F.C.|Aston Villa]] for a £9&nbsp;million transfer fee.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.avfc.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0,,10265~4855398,00.html|title=Breaking news: Villa sign Gueye|date=10 July 2015|accessdate=10 July 2015|publisher=Aston Villa F.C.|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160317150521/http://www.avfc.co.uk/page/NewsDetail/0%2C%2C10265~4855398%2C00.html|archivedate=17 March 2016|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/33362759|title=Idrissa Gueye: Aston Villa sign Lille midfielder for undisclosed fee|date=10 July 2015|accessdate=13 July 2015|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-3168190/Aston-Villa-midfielder-Idrissa-Gueye-admits-club-s-desire-sign-helped-ignore-Southampton-Marseille.html|title=Aston Villa midfielder Idrissa Gueye admits club's desire to sign him helped him ignore from Southampton and Marseille|accessdate=1 July 2017|website=Daily Mail}}</ref> On 8 August, he made his debut in a 1–0 away victory over [[A.F.C. Bournemouth|AFC Bournemouth]].<ref>{{cite|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2015/08/08/england/premier-league/afc-bournemouth/aston-villa-football-club/2043045/|title=AFC Bournemouth 0–1 Aston Villa|date=8 August 2015}}</ref> On 19 January 2016, Gueye scored his first and only goal for Villa in a 2–0 over [[Wycombe Wanderers F.C.|Wycombe Wanderers]] in the third round replay of the [[2015–16 FA Cup|FA Cup]].<ref>{{cite|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/35289310|title=Aston Villa 2–0 Wycombe Wanders |date=19 January 2016}}</ref> In total, Gueye made 35 league appearances for Villa as the club was relegated from the Premier League at the end of [[2015–16 Premier League|the season]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Idrissa Gueye: Aston Villa cannot keep midfielder after release clause triggered|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/36904124|accessdate=5 June 2017|publisher=BBC Sport|date=27 July 2016}}</ref>
===Everton=== On 2 August 2016 and with Aston Villa relegated from the Premier League, [[Everton F.C.|Everton]] triggered a release clause in Gueye's contract, reported to be £7.1&nbsp;million,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/36904124|title=Idrissa Gana: Aston Villa cannot keep midfielder after release clause triggered|date=27 July 2016|accessdate=30 July 2016|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> and signed him to a four-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/36958094|title=Idrissa Gueye: Everton sign midfielder from Aston Villa|date=2 August 2016|accessdate=2 August 2016|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> He made the highest number of successful tackles and interceptions per match across Europe's top five leagues over the 2016 calendar year.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://metro.co.uk/2017/01/01/chelseas-ngolo-kante-surprisingly-only-second-in-tackles-made-in-2016-6355184/|title=Chelsea's N'Golo Kante surprisingly only second in tackles made in 2016|date=1 January 2017|accessdate=1 January 2017|publisher=Metro}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/evertons-idrissa-gueye-best-ball-12407013|title=Why Everton's Idrissa Gueye is the best ball-winning midfielder in Europe|date=4 January 2017|accessdate=4 January 2017|website=Liverpool Echo}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/row-zed/evertons-idrissa-gueye-statistically-best-9563709|title=Everton's Idrissa Gueye is statistically the best holding midfielder in the whole of EUROPE|date=4 January 2017|accessdate=4 January 2017|website=Mirror}}</ref> Gueye scored his first league goal for Everton in a 2–0 victory over [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]] at [[Goodison Park]] on 25 February 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/39012183|title=nEverton 2–0 Sunderland|date=25 February 2017|accessdate=25 February 2017|publisher=BBC}}</ref> He became the first player in Europe's top five leagues to win 100 tackles in the 2016–17 season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.com/club/everton/368/blog/post/3069681/everton-finish-off-sunderland-as-idrissa-gueye-and-morgan-schneiderlin-continue-to-gel|title=Idrissa Gueye, Morgan Schneiderlin class as Everton beat Sunderland|date=27 February 2017|accessdate=5 March 2017|publisher=ESPN}}</ref>
Gueye scored his first goal for Everton in European competition on 17 August 2017 in the [[UEFA Europa League]] play-off round first leg against [[HNK Hajduk Split|Hajduk Split]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Everton 2–0 Hajduk Split|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/40940244 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=17 August 2017 |accessdate=18 August 2017}}</ref> In February 2018, he extended his contract with Everton until 2022.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/43133974|title=Idrissa Gueye: Everton midfielder signs long-term deal until 2022|date=20 February 2018|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref>
In January 2019, Everton rejected an offer from French club [[Paris St-Germain F.C.|PSG]] for Gueye.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/47030430|title=Idrissa Gueye: Everton reject Paris St-Germain bid for midfielder|date=28 January 2019|accessdate=29 January 2019|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref>
==International career== Gueye made his international debut for [[Senegal national football team|Senegal]] in 2011,<ref name=NFT/> and has appeared in FIFA World Cup qualifying matches for them.<ref name = "FIFA">{{FIFA player|332314}}</ref> He also represented them at the [[Football at the 2012 Summer Olympics&nbsp;– Men's tournament|2012 Olympics]],<ref name = "FIFA"/> at the [[2015 Africa Cup of Nations]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/30743603|title=2015 Africa Cup of Nations: Sadio Mane included in Senegal squad|date=9 January 2015|accessdate=2 July 2015|publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> and at the [[2017 Africa Cup of Nations]].
In May 2018, he was named in Senegal's 23-man squad for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup|2018 World Cup]] in Russia.<ref>{{cite web|title=Revealed: Every World Cup 2018 squad - 23-man & preliminary lists & when will they be announced?|url=http://www.goal.com/en-gb/amp/news/revealed-every-world-cup-2018-squad-23-man-preliminary-lists/oa0atsduflsv1nsf6oqk576rb|website=Goal|accessdate=18 May 2018}}</ref>
==Style of play== An energetic [[midfielder]], known for his ball-winning skills, as well as his ability to press opponents and intercept passes, Gueye completed the most tackles during the 2016–17 Premier League season.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11671/10826302/why-idrissa-gueye-is-so-important-to-everton-and-their-style-of-play |title=Why Idrissa Gueye is so important to Everton and their style of play|publisher=Skysports.com |last=Bate |first=Adam |date=8 April 2017 |accessdate=18 August 2017 }}</ref>
