{{Use Nigerian English|date=August 2018}} {{Use dmy dates|date=January 2018}} {{BLP sources|date=October 2016}} {{Infobox football biography | name = Henry Onyekuru | image = | image_size = | caption = | fullname = Henry Chukwuemeka Onyekuru<ref name="PL">{{cite web | title = Premier League Clubs submit Squad Lists | url = https://www.premierleague.com/news/465277v | publisher = Premier League | accessdate =10 September 2017}}</ref> | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1997|6|5|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Onitsha]], Nigeria | height = {{height|m=1.75}} | position = [[Forward (association football)|Forward]] | currentclub = [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]] (on loan from [[Everton F.C.|Everton]]) | clubnumber = 21 | youthyears1 = 2010–2015 | youthclubs1 = [[Aspire Academy]] | years1 = 2015–2017 | clubs1 = [[K.A.S. Eupen|Eupen]] | caps1 = 57 | goals1 = 28 | years2 = 2017– | clubs2 = [[Everton F.C.|Everton]] | caps2 = 0 | goals2 = 0 | years3 = 2017–2018 | clubs3 = → [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]] (loan) | caps3 = 19 | goals3 = 9 | years4 = 2018– | clubs4 = → [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]] (loan) | caps4 = 23 | goals4 = 11 | nationalyears1 = 2017– | nationalteam1 = [[Nigeria national football team|Nigeria]] | nationalcaps1 = 7 | nationalgoals1 = 1 | medaltemplates = | club-update = 15:49, 9 March 2019 (UTC) | nationalteam-update = 01:21, 22 March 2019 (UTC) }} '''Henry Chukwuemeka Onyekuru''' (born 5 June 1997) is a Nigerian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]], on [[loan (sports)|loan]] from [[Premier League]] club [[Everton FC|Everton]], and the [[Nigeria national football team|Nigeria national team]].
==Club career== ===Eupen=== Onyekuru began his football career with the [[Aspire Academy]] in 2010, and graduated in 2015 joining their partner club, [[K.A.S. Eupen]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://pageone.ng/2017/01/05/henry-onyekuru-national-stardom/|title=Henry Onyekuru - From National Stadium to Stardom - PageOne.ng|first=|last=PageOne|date=5 January 2017|publisher=}}</ref> He made his debut for Eupen on 5 September 2015 in a 2–2 tie against [[K.F.C. Dessel Sport]] in the [[Belgian Second Division]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2015/09/05/belgium/second-division/kfc-dessel-sport/koninklijke-as-eupen/2062227/|title=Dessel Sport vs. AS Eupen - 5 september 2015 - Soccerway|website=Soccerway}}</ref> Onyekuru helped the team get promoted to the [[Belgian First Division A]] in his debut season, and made his professional debut in a 3–0 loss on 30 July 2016 against [[S.V. Zulte Waregem]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2016/07/30/belgium/pro-league/sv-zulte-waregem/koninklijke-as-eupen/2239201/|title=Zulte-Waregem vs. AS Eupen - 30 juli 2016 - Soccerway|website=Soccerway}}</ref> After a successful season in the Belgium first division, Onyekuru finished as one of the top scorers in the league, catching the attention of various larger teams in Europe.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.espnfc.us/story/3046335/celtic-and-rb-leipzig-eye-nigerian-henry-onyekuru-sources|title=Celtic, RB Leipzig eyeing KAS Eupen's Henry Onyekuru - Sources|publisher=}}</ref> He finished the 2016–17 season as joint top-scorer with 22 goals, but the trophy was handed to [[Łukasz Teodorczyk]] as he scored more away goals than Onyekuru.<ref>{{cite web|title=Łukasz Teodorczyk królem strzelców|url=http://www.90minut.pl/news/277/news2777126-Lukasz-Teodorczyk-krolem-strzelcow.html|website=www.90minut.pl}}</ref>
===Everton=== On 30 June 2017, Onyekuru joined [[Everton F.C.|Everton]] for £7 million and was immediately sent on loan to [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Henry Onyekuru: Everton sign Nigeria striker and loan him to Anderlecht|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/40418808|website=BBC Sport|date=30 June 2017}}</ref> Onyekuru had been handed the number 9 jersey at Anderlecht for the 2017–18 campaign.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.liverpoolecho.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/incoming-everton-striker-onyekuru-handed-13250176|title=Incoming Everton striker Onyekuru handed new squad number|date=28 June 2017|accessdate=12 July 2017|publisher=LiverpoolEcho}}</ref>
Having scored 10 goals in 28 matches for Anderlecht, Onyekuru suffered a knee ligament injury in December which would require surgery. Anderlecht announced surgery would be necessary and that he would be out of action "for several months".<ref>{{cite news|title=Everton Youngster Onyekuru Set for 8-Month Spell on Sidelines With Knee Injury|url=https://www.si.com/soccer/2017/12/29/everton-youngster-onyekuru-set-8-month-spell-sidelines-knee-injury|accessdate=25 January 2018|work=Sports Illustrated|date=29 December 2017}}</ref> In January 2018, it was reported that Onyekuru would return to Anderlecht after rehabilitation and full recovery.<ref>{{cite news|title=Onyekuru returns to Anderlecht after recovery from Injury|url=https://guardian.ng/sport/onyekuru-returns-to-anderlecht-after-recovery-from-injury/|accessdate=25 January 2018|work=The Guardian (Nigeria)|date=23 January 2018}}</ref>
In July 2018, Onyekuru joined [[Galatasaray S.K. (football)|Galatasaray]] on a season-long loan.<ref>{{cite news |title=Henry Onyekuru: Everton striker joins Galatasaray on loan |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/44805994 |accessdate=12 July 2018 |work=BBC Sport |date=12 July 2018}}</ref> The loan fee paid to Everton was reported as £700,000.<ref>{{cite web |title=Everton's Henry Onyekuru joins Galatasaray on season-long loan |url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/11434839/evertons-henry-onyekuru-joins-galatasaray-on-season-long-loan |website=Sky Sports |accessdate=12 July 2018 |date=12 July 2018}}</ref>
==International career== Onyekuru was called up for the Super Eagles camp in May 2017.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.espnfc.us/nigeria/story/3128973/onyekuru-gets-nigeria-call|title=Onyekuru gets Nigeria call|work=ESPNFC.com|access-date=2018-05-14}}</ref> He made his senior debut for Nigeria in a 3–0 friendly win over [[Togo national football team|Togo]] on 1 June 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/nigeria-vs-togo/teams/371810|title=Internationals (Sky Sports)|website=SkySports}}</ref>
